11
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:50,333
That's why Atzin's here.

12
00:00:50,333 --> 00:00:52,167
We have a chaperone present
for patients

13
00:00:52,167 --> 00:00:53,633
of the opposite sex.

14
00:00:53,633 --> 00:00:54,767
Hi.

15
00:00:54,767 --> 00:00:57,267
Don't worry,
I'm not looking at...

16
00:00:57,267 --> 00:00:59,067
- You know that?
- Ah!

17
00:00:59,067 --> 00:01:01,133
There's a name
for his condition.

18
00:01:01,133 --> 00:01:04,300
You know, the type
who showers with shorts on?

19
00:01:04,300 --> 00:01:06,167
You're totally looking at it.

20
00:01:06,167 --> 00:01:10,333
The type who needs to turn off
the lights when it's sexy time?

21
00:01:10,367 --> 00:01:13,667
- Oh my God, stop!
- I'm not doing anything!

22
00:01:13,667 --> 00:01:15,800
Angle lower.
There's no urine.

23
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:19,233
That means you're not
in the right zip code.

24
00:01:19,233 --> 00:01:21,467
And watch your sterile field.

25
00:01:21,467 --> 00:01:23,100
Do you want to do this?

26
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:25,067
You're talking to who?

27
00:01:25,567 --> 00:01:27,267
Is somebody else in here?

28
00:01:27,267 --> 00:01:29,100
- [EXHALES SHARPLY]
- Deep breaths.

29
00:01:29,100 --> 00:01:30,233
No, no, no.

30
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:32,833
Twist it while you push it in.

31
00:01:32,833 --> 00:01:34,533
Don't force it.

32
00:01:34,533 --> 00:01:38,133
His sphincter will clench up
like a traffic jam.

33
00:01:38,133 --> 00:01:40,467
- Got it.
- Never nude!

34
00:01:41,133 --> 00:01:42,533
That's the term.

35
00:01:42,533 --> 00:01:44,633
He's a never nude.

36
00:01:45,100 --> 00:01:46,367
[CHUCKLING]

37
00:01:46,367 --> 00:01:48,233
He's laughing at me!

38
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:52,067
- [ATZIN CHUCKLING]
- He's laughing at me!

39
00:01:53,167 --> 00:01:55,200
Did he hear what I said?

40
00:01:55,500 --> 00:02:00,333
[QUIRKY MUSIC CONTINUES]

41
00:02:07,300 --> 00:02:08,800
[TESS] Impossible.

42
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:10,333
[NOA] Are you sure?

43
00:02:10,333 --> 00:02:11,667
Since when?

44
00:02:11,667 --> 00:02:12,867
How did it happen?

45
00:02:12,867 --> 00:02:15,733
He's a liar. He lies.

46
00:02:15,767 --> 00:02:17,367
Is there a limit?

47
00:02:17,367 --> 00:02:18,733
A certain time?

48
00:02:19,367 --> 00:02:23,767
So, you're telling me
he's got powers now?

49
00:02:23,767 --> 00:02:25,867
[SCOFFS]
More like a curse.

50
00:02:26,433 --> 00:02:29,700
Imagine Tess in your ear
all day.

51
00:02:29,700 --> 00:02:30,900
[CHUCKLING]

52
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:32,167
Ouch!

53
00:02:34,367 --> 00:02:36,367
Good morning, Josh.

54
00:02:36,367 --> 00:02:38,433
Hello, good morning.
Thank you.

55
00:02:40,633 --> 00:02:43,600
Relax, guys.
She knows everything.

56
00:02:43,600 --> 00:02:45,600
Knows what?
There's nothing to know.

57
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:47,633
And who the hell is Josh?

58
00:02:47,667 --> 00:02:49,233
I told you he's a liar.

59
00:02:49,233 --> 00:02:51,167
Is this a thing now?

60
00:02:51,167 --> 00:02:53,433
We're just, like,
talking or whatever.

61
00:02:53,433 --> 00:02:55,600
Oh!

62
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:57,767
My grandma was a healer.

63
00:02:57,767 --> 00:02:59,833
Because of her,
I can see ghosts.

64
00:02:59,833 --> 00:03:00,900
Like you.

65
00:03:02,567 --> 00:03:04,333
- Yes, Dee?
- I don't get it.

66
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:08,567
I have some crayons
in the supply room.

67
00:03:08,567 --> 00:03:10,767
He'll catch up to you later.

68
00:03:10,767 --> 00:03:13,333
And what the hell
is a curarachi?

69
00:03:13,833 --> 00:03:16,600
A<i> curandera.</i>
<i>It's like a babaylan.</i>

70
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:17,767
- Oh.
- Duh, Ros.

71
00:03:17,767 --> 00:03:19,333
It's like a white lighter.

72
00:03:19,333 --> 00:03:21,167
I've been watching
reruns of Charmed.

73
00:03:23,533 --> 00:03:26,933
I've always felt this ward
sits at a crossroads.

74
00:03:26,933 --> 00:03:29,433
You know,
where spirits pass through.

75
00:03:29,433 --> 00:03:31,900
Now that I can see them too,
I can actually help.

76
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:35,200
We can start by celebrating
<i> Día de los Muertos.</i>

77
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,633
Uh... It's not that simple.

78
00:03:37,833 --> 00:03:39,467
I can handle it. It's easy.

79
00:03:40,433 --> 00:03:42,300
I partied so hard in Ibiza

80
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:44,567
that I woke up
to a spiritual cleansing

81
00:03:44,567 --> 00:03:45,900
from a ghost named Miguel.

82
00:03:46,633 --> 00:03:48,367
