263
00:13:47,933 --> 00:13:50,333
- [CAMILLE SIGHS DEEPLY]
- [GLOVES SQUEAKING]

264
00:13:50,333 --> 00:13:53,900
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

265
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:55,033
You know what?

266
00:13:55,433 --> 00:13:57,600
You want to hear
something crazy?

267
00:13:57,600 --> 00:14:03,133
I just realized why I love
being a nurse so much.

268
00:14:04,567 --> 00:14:09,367
Yes, we study science
and the licenses.

269
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:15,067
But it's the one thing
that makes me stay.

270
00:14:15,333 --> 00:14:17,333
Even when things get hard.

271
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:19,933
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

272
00:14:19,933 --> 00:14:23,067
When answers don't help.

273
00:14:23,933 --> 00:14:26,300
When all somebody wants...

274
00:14:26,833 --> 00:14:28,433
is to not be alone.

275
00:14:30,100 --> 00:14:31,233
So...

276
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:34,000
I'm here to stay.

277
00:14:34,267 --> 00:14:35,933
I'm here to listen.

278
00:14:35,933 --> 00:14:42,900
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

279
00:14:55,567 --> 00:14:57,900
When my grandpa was dying...

280
00:14:58,100 --> 00:14:59,967
he kept seeing ghosts.

281
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:05,000
He said it was his mom,
his sister,

282
00:15:06,033 --> 00:15:08,267
and my grandma
coming to get him.

283
00:15:12,233 --> 00:15:14,300
We have a term for that,
you know.

284
00:15:16,133 --> 00:15:17,367
"Sundo."

285
00:15:20,467 --> 00:15:24,333
It's not dying
that I'm worried about.

286
00:15:25,167 --> 00:15:27,200
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

287
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:28,867
[SOBS]

288
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:30,933
Then...

289
00:15:31,933 --> 00:15:34,000
What's breaking your heart?

290
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:40,967
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

291
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:45,033
I'm not a slut, you know.

292
00:15:46,133 --> 00:15:48,500
I just trusted the wrong person.

293
00:15:51,467 --> 00:15:55,033
You're not made up of
the opinions of other people.

294
00:15:57,533 --> 00:16:03,233
Those who love you,
will love you no matter what.

295
00:16:03,233 --> 00:16:08,600
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

296
00:16:08,633 --> 00:16:11,267
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

297
00:16:12,033 --> 00:16:13,700
In essence, closing Ward Five

298
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:15,967
and making way for
private doctor's offices

299
00:16:15,967 --> 00:16:18,533
will put us far in the black
for years to come.

300
00:16:21,633 --> 00:16:22,667
Any questions?

301
00:16:23,133 --> 00:16:24,967
That's a great presentation,
Walt.

302
00:16:24,967 --> 00:16:26,400
Did you make that in Canva?

303
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:29,367
Any real questions?

304
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:34,600
I hate to say it, but if it
keeps us open a few more years,

305
00:16:35,167 --> 00:16:36,333
it might be the right call.

306
00:16:37,467 --> 00:16:38,967
It's not looking good, Jane.

307
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:42,333
This is still a business
at the end of the day.

308
00:16:43,033 --> 00:16:44,233
Shall we put it to a vote?

309
00:16:44,500 --> 00:16:45,733
Let's get this over with.

310
00:16:46,233 --> 00:16:49,233
I actually have a
counter-business proposition--

311
00:16:49,233 --> 00:16:50,200
Oh!

312
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:53,300
Would you like us
to call your assistant?

313
00:16:53,300 --> 00:16:54,667
No, no. It's fine.

314
00:16:54,667 --> 00:16:56,367
Just give me a second.
I'm sorry.

315
00:16:56,367 --> 00:16:59,000
Jane, we don't have all day.

316
00:16:59,500 --> 00:17:01,500
Then, tomorrow.

317
00:17:02,167 --> 00:17:07,667
I would love to continue this
conversation tomorrow. Please.

318
00:17:07,667 --> 00:17:10,500
I do have a patient
waiting for orders.

319
00:17:11,367 --> 00:17:12,667
And I have another meeting.

320
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:16,000
Oh, why not?
A day won't kill us.

321
00:17:25,533 --> 00:17:26,667
Oh.

322
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:28,667
Oh, well.

323
00:17:28,667 --> 00:17:31,167
That answers our question
if we should do this or not.

324
00:17:31,167 --> 00:17:33,167
This is so mean!

325
00:17:33,167 --> 00:17:35,667
Maybe I should possess
that witch.

326
00:17:36,533 --> 00:17:37,433
[CAMILLE GASPS]

327
00:17:39,133 --> 00:17:40,200
What happened?

328
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:42,400
What do you mean what happened?
This was you.

329
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:43,800
No, I would never.

330
00:17:43,800 --> 00:17:45,700
You certainly didn't
hide your displeasure.

331
00:17:45,700 --> 00:17:48,467
I changed my mind. I...

332
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:53,533
I realized that God
is gracious, kind, empathetic.

333
00:17:55,167 --> 00:17:56,400
What is this?

334
00:17:56,600 --> 00:18:00,233
[CAMILLE] It's Hubert's
grandfather. The 505.

335
00:18:00,533 --> 00:18:02,233
The Never Nude!

336
00:18:03,733 --> 00:18:05,333
Thanks, Camille.
But it doesn't matter.

337
00:18:05,333 --> 00:18:06,500
We're cleaning all of this up.

338
00:18:06,500 --> 00:18:08,600
And I'm gonna tell everyone
it's canceled tomorrow.

339
00:18:13,633 --> 00:18:14,567
Noa.

340
00:18:17,300 --> 00:18:18,667
Somebody clean up this mess.

341
00:18:18,667 --> 00:18:20,033
I got this, boss.

342
00:18:20,433 --> 00:18:21,533
[SIGHS]

343
00:18:21,567 --> 00:18:22,733
Well...

344
00:18:22,733 --> 00:18:26,167
(In Spanish) Add disappointed
ghosts to my to-do list.

345
00:18:29,267 --> 00:18:31,333
[GLASSES CLINKING]

346
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:41,300
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

347
00:18:45,667 --> 00:18:46,633
[SIGHS]

348
00:18:47,533 --> 00:18:51,600
[COUGHING]

349
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:52,800
Ugh.

350
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:56,500
The apple fell far from the tree
on the tequila tolerance.

351
00:18:56,533 --> 00:18:59,400
This is what you and
my mom used to do?

352
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:00,433
[CHUCKLES]

353
00:19:01,433 --> 00:19:03,433
Well, it was a different time.

354
00:19:03,700 --> 00:19:06,767
Back in the day, medical folk
weren't afraid of bars

355
00:19:06,767 --> 00:19:08,533
before you know what.

356
00:19:08,533 --> 00:19:09,467
[CHUCKLES]

357
00:19:12,567 --> 00:19:13,767
What are we gonna do?

358
00:19:14,633 --> 00:19:16,367
We fight, kid.

359
00:19:18,333 --> 00:19:19,400
[SIGHS]

360
00:19:20,767 --> 00:19:22,167
What if we lose?

361
00:19:23,833 --> 00:19:26,700
Then we learn to do
what everyone has to do

362
00:19:26,700 --> 00:19:28,333
at some point in their life.

363
00:19:30,233 --> 00:19:31,633
We learn to say goodbye.

364
00:19:42,500 --> 00:19:45,200
[COUGHING]

365
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:50,167
[ENGINE HUMMING]

366
00:19:55,667 --> 00:19:59,800
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

367
00:20:03,867 --> 00:20:10,900
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

368
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:20,400
[STIRRING MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

369
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:21,433
[MUSIC STOPS]

370
00:20:30,667 --> 00:20:32,400
Ah! Ouch!

371
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:35,267
Mom, why didn't you wake me?

372
00:20:35,300 --> 00:20:36,533
I just did.

373
00:20:37,633 --> 00:20:40,400
You smell like you've
been working three jobs

374
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:42,833
and cheating on all of them.

375
00:20:45,933 --> 00:20:47,400
Hold the door, please.
Thank you.

376
00:20:47,833 --> 00:20:48,767
Oh, sorry.

377
00:20:49,533 --> 00:20:50,467
Excuse me.

378
00:20:50,467 --> 00:20:51,433
Where is she?

379
00:20:51,900 --> 00:20:54,400
[NOA PANTING]

380
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:55,333
Hi.

381
00:20:56,500 --> 00:20:57,667
[NOA] Good luck.

382
00:20:57,667 --> 00:20:58,833
Now you have weapons.

383
00:20:59,933 --> 00:21:00,900
Let's go.

384
00:21:10,667 --> 00:21:12,533
- What's going on here?
- Oh!

385
00:21:14,033 --> 00:21:15,467
Food's here.

386
00:21:15,667 --> 00:21:17,900
Food already? You haven't
even brushed your teeth.

387
00:21:21,700 --> 00:21:28,600
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

388
00:21:41,267 --> 00:21:47,833
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

389
00:21:47,867 --> 00:21:49,500
What happened to pass down?

390
00:21:55,033 --> 00:21:59,667
Ward Five nursing turnover
dropped 23 percent

391
00:21:59,667 --> 00:22:01,533
in the past few months,

392
00:22:01,533 --> 00:22:04,000
the only unit trending downward.

393
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:11,800
Patient satisfaction scores rose
from 54 percent to 89 percent,

394
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:16,433
with highest marks in
communication and compassion.

395
00:22:16,467 --> 00:22:20,667
Average length of
stay decreased by.6 days,

396
00:22:20,667 --> 00:22:26,367
translating into a savings
of 312 dollars per patient.

397
00:22:28,767 --> 00:22:33,033
So whatever personal BS you
have against her, Mr. Alderman,

398
00:22:33,533 --> 00:22:36,400
even you can't
deny Noa's numbers.

399
00:22:36,400 --> 00:22:43,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

400
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:53,033
[JANE] And since we're
talking about feelings,

401
00:22:53,667 --> 00:22:55,333
let me tell you the truth.

402
00:22:55,867 --> 00:22:58,600
Nurses don't stay
because of dollars.

403
00:22:59,533 --> 00:23:01,767
[MUSIC TURNS SOFT]

404
00:23:01,767 --> 00:23:04,000
They stay because they matter.

405
00:23:05,567 --> 00:23:06,633
Oh.

406
00:23:06,633 --> 00:23:07,967
Good morning, boss.

407
00:23:07,967 --> 00:23:09,800
Sorry we didn't respond
to your text last night.

408
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:11,633
We got your text
like super late.

409
00:23:12,733 --> 00:23:14,533
I said no one needed
to bring anything.

410
00:23:14,533 --> 00:23:16,033
I was gonna bring the food.

411
00:23:16,033 --> 00:23:17,400
No offense,

412
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:19,800
but I wouldn't trust you
to bring the good Mexican stuff.

413
00:23:19,800 --> 00:23:22,067
- True!
- [LAUGHING]

414
00:23:22,100 --> 00:23:23,767
[JANE] In their ward,

415
00:23:24,800 --> 00:23:28,067
they remember the nurse
who never clocked out.

416
00:23:28,067 --> 00:23:35,033
- [SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]

417
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:39,400
Gosh, you guys did all of this?

418
00:23:40,467 --> 00:23:43,567
Hey, it was all my idea.

419
00:23:43,567 --> 00:23:45,100
Say hello to my followers!

420
00:23:45,100 --> 00:23:48,433
[JANE] They remember the nurse
who just wants to be liked.

421
00:23:49,500 --> 00:23:52,533
The selfless ones who volunteer
for double shifts

422
00:23:52,533 --> 00:23:53,600
just for the team.

423
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:54,767
I brought champorado.

424
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:57,633
Oh, is that Filipino or Mexican?

425
00:23:58,733 --> 00:23:59,800
They both have it?

426
00:24:00,200 --> 00:24:02,600
- Oh my god.
- [ROS FAKES SOB]

427
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:05,567
[JANE] The ones who
sacrificed and left their homes

428
00:24:05,567 --> 00:24:07,967
just to care for strangers.

429
00:24:07,967 --> 00:24:14,133
- [SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [LAUGHING]

430
00:24:14,133 --> 00:24:16,000
[JANE] All to look after
the patients

431
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:18,567
whose lives are about to change.

432
00:24:18,567 --> 00:24:21,033
For better or for worse.

433
00:24:21,033 --> 00:24:24,167
[OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

434
00:24:24,167 --> 00:24:26,633
And most importantly...

435
00:24:27,900 --> 00:24:30,900
They make everyone
feel remembered.

436
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:38,167
With them, healing starts
with being seen.

437
00:24:40,067 --> 00:24:41,500
Excuse me.

438
00:24:44,167 --> 00:24:50,933
- [MUSIC TURNS EMOTIONAL]
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]

439
00:25:17,967 --> 00:25:24,900
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

440
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:27,133
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

441
00:25:39,700 --> 00:25:45,167
[NOA SOBS SOFTLY]

442
00:25:49,867 --> 00:25:56,867
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

443
00:26:10,867 --> 00:26:12,833
[JANE] They stay
because they matter.

444
00:26:19,133 --> 00:26:21,167
You all told me
you would close the ward

445
00:26:21,167 --> 00:26:22,900
if we didn't get metrics up,

446
00:26:22,900 --> 00:26:24,300
but they are up.

447
00:26:25,233 --> 00:26:27,733
And I'm gonna need you all
to keep your word.

448
00:26:29,167 --> 00:26:36,267
[CLAPPING]

449
00:26:39,567 --> 00:26:40,700
The numbers are fine,

450
00:26:41,000 --> 00:26:42,233
but we don't even know
if they’ll pass

451
00:26:42,267 --> 00:26:44,267
the next joint
commission inspection.

452
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:49,867
Sure, but that's a year away.
We can reassess then.

453
00:26:49,867 --> 00:26:50,833
[CHUCKLES]

454
00:26:50,833 --> 00:26:52,233
Are you sure it's a year?

455
00:26:53,967 --> 00:26:55,267
Calendars speed up.

456
00:26:55,700 --> 00:26:58,800
Especially when complaints
stack up.

457
00:27:06,267 --> 00:27:13,067
["THE DENIAL SONG"
INSTRUMENTAL PLAYING]

458
00:27:24,767 --> 00:27:31,700
["THE DENIAL SONG"
INSTRUMENTAL CONTINUES]

459
00:27:44,867 --> 00:27:51,700
["THE DENIAL SONG"
INSTRUMENTAL CONTINUES]

460
00:28:04,200 --> 00:28:11,100
["THE DENIAL SONG"
INSTRUMENTAL CONTINUES]

461
00:28:26,133 --> 00:28:33,000
["THE DENIAL SONG"
INSTRUMENTAL CONTINUES]

462
00:28:51,433 --> 00:28:58,400
["THE DENIAL SONG"
INSTRUMENTAL CONTINUES]

463
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:21,833
["THE DENIAL SONG"
INSTRUMENTAL CONTINUES]

464
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:40,233
[MUSIC FADES]

465
00:29:41,933 --> 00:29:48,900
[WHIMSICAL MUSIC PLAYING]

